{"tid":1815164,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"[突發] 因應近日中東局勢 德國宣佈會撤走部分駐伊拉克德軍","createTime":"2020-01-07T10:05:36.000Z","updateTime":"2020-01-07T15:29:23.000Z","uid":133680,"like":1,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"d927989572583ba9ac7faf7849eaf600768afd7d","tid":1815164,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:05:36.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.google.com/amp/s/amp.dw.com/en/germany-to-partially-withdraw-troops-from-iraq/a-51909308\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Famp%2Fs%2Famp.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermany-to-partially-withdraw-troops-from-iraq%2Fa-51909308&d=rLp99s1CaA%2FTm5LA4NL6TUBo7c%2BYFxEppcXi0rJe94o%3D&h=89002069\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com/amp/s/amp.dw.com/en/germany-to-partially-withdraw-troops-from-iraq/a-51909308</a><br />\n<br />\nLIVE TV<br />\nTOP STORIES<br />\nGermany to partially withdraw troops from Iraq<br />\n2 hours ago<br />\n<br />\n00:34 mins.<br />\nDW NEWS | 1 hour ago<br />\nHeiko Maas: 'The safety of our soldiers is our highest priority'<br />\nGermany responded to growing security concerns in the Gulf region, saying it plans to &quot;temporarily thin out&quot; the number of soldiers in Iraq. Its military presence will be reduced particularly in Baghdad and Taji.<br />\nGermany will reduce the number of its troops stationed in Iraq due to growing regional security concerns, according to two of the country's top lawmakers.<br />\n<br />\nThe German military contingent in the country will be &quot;temporarily thinned out,&quot; with around 30 out of the 130 personnel serving in the country to be redeployed to neighboring countries, Foreign Minister Heiko Maas and Defense Minister Annegret Kramp-Karrenbauer said in a letter to their ministries.<br />\n<br />\nThe transfer will mainly apply to soldiers stationed in Iraq's capital Baghdad and Taji, to the north. Soldiers in these areas are set to be moved to Jordan and Kuwait. <br />\n<br />\nIraq's parliament voted for anti-IS coalition soldiers to leave the country following the fatal drone attack on Qassem Soleimani.<br />\n<br />\nCurrently, the German Bundeswehr supports regional efforts against Islamic State in Iraq, providing military training, Tornado reconnaissance jets and tanker aircraft for air-to-air refueling. Most of Germany's soldiers in Iraq are stationed in the northern Kurdish region of the country.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Naturally we will respect any sovereign decision of the Iraqi government,&quot; said Maas, while warning that the reduction of international forces could lead to Islamic State gaining a stronger foothold in the region and cause &quot;greater instability&quot; in Iraq.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n02:23 mins.<br />\nDW NEWS | 04.01.2020<br />\nIraqi mourners take to the streets of Baghdad<br />\nWhy is Germany reducing troop numbers?<br />\n<br />\nDW political correspondent Thomas Sparrow said one reason that Germany was reducing troop numbers was &quot;security, the security of German soldiers, similar to what NATO has already done as well.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nThe fear is that some soldiers being trained by German troops have sympathies with Iranian and Iraqi militias and could turn the weapons on the service personnel training them. <br />\n<br />\nSparrow said another reason is that the German government has removed them, awaiting a final decision by the Iraqi government on foreign coalition forces fighting IS in Iraq.<br />\n<br />\nThe redeployment is intended only as a temporary measure, with the letter from Maas and Kramp-Karrenbauer saying &quot;in principle, we are prepared to continue providing our proven support within an internationally coordinated framework as long as this is something that Iraq wants and is in the situation to permit it.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n&quot;When the training is able to resume, the military personnel can be reinstated,&quot; added the ministers."},{"pid":"5203b5c25cd691f5537a1d3b7f6a222f5f83060c","tid":1815164,"uid":315833,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:09:30.000Z","msg":"咁啲軍有咩用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3b76f1ac5e23fe3d9960f182e8860b3cec9d5b0d","tid":1815164,"uid":167548,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:11:42.000Z","msg":"德國唔是北約嘅咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1706fb44ba93e8999bc4eaed978e6426bc5f2f5c","tid":1815164,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:13:51.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"16b62443774748a5b8a238bce19c66dd1ce26084","tid":1815164,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:26:51.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"604d7731d054fabb6656fa40d84bb9f913ba4922","tid":1815164,"uid":58247,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"5203b5c25cd691f5537a1d3b7f6a222f5f83060c","tid":1815164,"uid":315833,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:09:30.000Z","msg":"咁啲軍有咩用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T10:33:04.000Z","msg":"本身呃飲呃食度下假點知黎真既仲唔走咩<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"76a0d4cbc92e6d1e2fed06f531332ec1d7354aeb","tid":1815164,"uid":311004,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"604d7731d054fabb6656fa40d84bb9f913ba4922","tid":1815164,"uid":58247,"l